---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const privacySchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  name: "Privacy Policy - Ad Revenue Calculator",
  url: "https://adsrevenuecalculator.com/privacy",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Ad Revenue Calculator"
  description="Our Privacy Policy outlines how Ads Revenue Calculator handles user data, cookies, and analytics."
  schema={privacySchema}
  canonicalUrl="https://adsrevenuecalculator.com/privacy"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-6 leading-7 text-[var(--color-body)] mt-12 p-4">

    <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-ink)] md:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>
      At <strong>Ads Revenue Calculator</strong>, accessible from
      <a
        href="https://adsrevenuecalculator.com"
        class="text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline"
      >
      {" "}
        adsrevenuecalculator.com
      </a>,
      one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors. This Privacy
      Policy document contains the types of information that are collected and
      recorded by Ads Revenue Calculator and how we use them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-ink)]">
      1. Information We Collect
    </h2>

    <p>
      We do not require you to create an account or provide personal
      information to use our calculator tools. The inputs you provide
      (views, RPMs, etc.) are processed locally in your browser and are not
      saved to our servers.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-ink)]">
      2. Log Files & Analytics
    </h2>

    <p>
      Ads Revenue Calculator follows a standard procedure of using log files
      and analytics tracking. The information collected includes IP addresses,
      browser type, ISP, timestamps, referring and exit pages, and possibly
      the number of clicks. These data points are not linked to personally
      identifiable information and are used to analyze trends, administer the
      website, and understand visitor behavior.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-ink)]">
      3. Cookies and Web Beacons
    </h2>

    <p>
      Like most websites, Ads Revenue Calculator uses cookies to store visitor
      preferences and information about visited pages. This information helps
      us optimize the user experience by customizing content based on browser
      type and other anonymous usage data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-ink)]">
      4. Third-Party Ad Networks
    </h2>

    <p>
      We may use third-party advertising companies to serve ads when you visit
      our website. These companies may use aggregated information—not
     </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>